1939;;Three Sons;;American;;Jack Hively;;Edward Ellis, Katharine Alexander;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Sons;;Daniel Pardway (Edward Ellis) a department store owner is deeply saddened to learn that none of his grown sons are interested in taking over the business he has worked so hard to build. To coerce them, he even tries giving them shares of company stock. In the end, only the youngest son shows any interest at all.[2]